# Trivy baseline -- gate-on-new: accept CURRENT HIGH/CRITICAL findings; the build
# trivy gate fails only on a NEW fixed-available CVE. Trimmed 2026-07-13 (SMP-1297 /
# Forgejo #474) against a live trivy scan of the deployed image: 70 stale entries
# removed (no longer present -- fixed by the chamber source-build (#291) + apt-upgrade
# in the runtime stage since the #674 refresh, incl. libmariadb3 / CVE-2025-13699).
#
# SMP-1297 remediation: activestorage/activesupport (Rails 7.2.3.1), faraday, fast-xml-parser
# and puma (7.2.1) were pulled forward AS REGULAR GEMS -- their CVEs are gone from the image, so
# they were removed from this baseline.
#
# INCIDENT 2026-07-13: uri and zlib are Ruby DEFAULT gems. Pinning them forward in the Gemfile
# (uri 0.13.3 / zlib 3.2.3) fixes the RUNTIME -- bundler activates the patched versions -- but does
# NOT remove the vulnerable default-gem FILES (uri-0.13.1.gemspec / zlib-3.1.1.gemspec) that ship
# with Ruby, so trivy still finds them in the image. They were prematurely removed from this
# baseline in #319, which failed the dev build's image-scan gate and BLOCKED dev deploys. Re-added
# here. The proper fix -- remove/upgrade the default gems in the Dockerfile so the image is clean --
# is tracked in #474; once it lands, uri/zlib/erb/net-imap/braces/form-data can all be dropped and
# this baseline emptied.
#
# The entries below are the HIGH/CRIT genuinely present in the image (all fixable). #474.
# pkg -> fixed version:
#   braces: 3.0.3
#   erb: ~> 4.0.3.1, ~> 4.0.4.1, ~> 6.0.1.1, >= 6.0.4
#   form-data: 2.5.6, 3.0.5, 4.0.6
#   net-imap: ~> 0.3.10, ~> 0.4.24, ~> 0.5.14, >= 0.6.4
#   uri (DEFAULT gem, image-only): ~> 0.12.5, ~> 0.13.3, >= 1.0.4
#   zlib (DEFAULT gem, image-only): ~> 3.0.1, ~> 3.1.2, >= 3.2.3

